17namespace v8::internal::compiler::turboshaft {
18
19#include "src/compiler/turboshaft/define-assembler-macros.inc"
20
21template <class Next>
22class LoopUnrollingReducer;
23
24// LoopPeeling "peels" the first iteration of innermost loops (= it extracts the
25// first iteration from the loop). The goal of this is mainly to hoist checks
26// out of the loop (such as Smi-checks, type-checks, bound-checks, etc).
27
28template <class Next>
29class LoopPeelingReducer : public Next {
30 public:
31 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(LoopPeeling)
32
33#if defined(__clang__)
34 // LoopUnrolling and LoopPeeling shouldn't be performed in the same phase, see
35 // the comment in pipeline.cc where LoopUnrolling is triggered.
36 static_assert(
37 !reducer_list_contains<ReducerList, LoopUnrollingReducer>::value);
38#endif
39
40 V<None> REDUCE_INPUT_GRAPH(Goto)(V<None> ig_idx, const GotoOp& gto) {
41 // Note that the "ShouldSkipOptimizationStep" is placed in the part of
42 // this Reduce method triggering the peeling rather than at the begining.
43 // This is because the backedge skipping is not an optimization but a
44 // mandatory lowering when peeling is being performed.
45 LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) { return Next::ReduceInputGraphGoto(ig_idx, gto); }
46
47 const Block* dst = gto.destination;
48 if (dst->IsLoop() && !gto.is_backedge && CanPeelLoop(dst)) {
49 if (ShouldSkipOptimizationStep()) goto no_change;
50 PeelFirstIteration(dst);
51 return {};
52 } else if (IsPeeling() && dst == current_loop_header_) {
53 // We skip the backedge of the loop: PeelFirstIeration will instead emit a
54 // forward edge to the non-peeled header.
55 return {};
56 }
57
58 goto no_change;
59 }
60
61 // TODO(dmercadier): remove once StackCheckOp are kept in the pipeline until
62 // the very end (which should happen when we have a SimplifiedLowering in
63 // Turboshaft).
64 V<AnyOrNone> REDUCE_INPUT_GRAPH(Call)(V<AnyOrNone> ig_idx,
65 const CallOp& call) {
66 LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) { return Next::ReduceInputGraphCall(ig_idx, call); }
67 if (ShouldSkipOptimizationStep()) goto no_change;
68
69 if (IsPeeling() && call.IsStackCheck(__ input_graph(), broker_,
70 StackCheckKind::kJSIterationBody)) {
71 // We remove the stack check of the peeled iteration.
72 return {};
73 }
74
75 goto no_change;
76 }
77
78 OpIndex REDUCE_INPUT_GRAPH(StackCheck)(OpIndex ig_idx,
79 const StackCheckOp& stack_check) {
80 LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) {
81 return Next::ReduceInputGraphStackCheck(ig_idx, stack_check);
82 }
83 if (ShouldSkipOptimizationStep()) goto no_change;
84
85 if (IsPeeling()) {
86 // We remove the stack check of the peeled iteration.
87 return OpIndex::Invalid();
88 }
89
90 goto no_change;
91 }
92
93 OpIndex REDUCE_INPUT_GRAPH(Phi)(OpIndex ig_idx, const PhiOp& phi) {
94 if (!IsEmittingUnpeeledBody() ||
95 __ current_input_block() != current_loop_header_) {
96 return Next::ReduceInputGraphPhi(ig_idx, phi);
97 }
98
99 // The 1st input of the loop phis of the unpeeled loop header should be the
100 // 2nd input of the original loop phis, since with the peeling, they
101 // actually come from the backedge of the peeled iteration.
102 return __ PendingLoopPhi(
103 __ MapToNewGraph(phi.input(PhiOp::kLoopPhiBackEdgeIndex)), phi.rep);
104 }
105
106 private:
107 static constexpr int kMaxSizeForPeeling = 1000;
108 enum class PeelingStatus {
109 kNotPeeling,
110 kEmittingPeeledLoop,
111 kEmittingUnpeeledBody
112 };
113
114 void PeelFirstIteration(const Block* header) {
115 DCHECK_EQ(peeling_, PeelingStatus::kNotPeeling);
116 ScopedModification<PeelingStatus> scope(&peeling_,
117 PeelingStatus::kEmittingPeeledLoop);
118 current_loop_header_ = header;
119
120 // Emitting the peeled iteration.
121 auto loop_body = loop_finder_.GetLoopBody(header);
122 // Note that this call to CloneSubGraph will not emit the backedge because
123 // we'll skip it in ReduceInputGraphGoto (above). The next CloneSubGraph
124 // call will start with a forward Goto to the header (like all
125 // CloneSubGraphs do), and will end by emitting the backedge, because this
126 // time {peeling_} won't be EmittingPeeledLoop, and the backedge Goto will
127 // thus be emitted.
128 __ CloneSubGraph(loop_body, /* keep_loop_kinds */ false);
129
130 if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) {
131 // While peeling, we realized that the 2nd iteration of the loop is not
132 // reachable.
133 return;
134 }
135
136 // We now emit the regular unpeeled loop.
137 peeling_ = PeelingStatus::kEmittingUnpeeledBody;
138 __ CloneSubGraph(loop_body, /* keep_loop_kinds */ true,
139 /* is_loop_after_peeling */ true);
140 }
141
142 bool CanPeelLoop(const Block* header) {
143 if (IsPeeling()) return false;
144 auto info = loop_finder_.GetLoopInfo(header);
145 return !info.has_inner_loops && info.op_count <= kMaxSizeForPeeling;
146 }
147
148 bool IsPeeling() const {
149 return peeling_ == PeelingStatus::kEmittingPeeledLoop;
150 }
151 bool IsEmittingUnpeeledBody() const {
152 return peeling_ == PeelingStatus::kEmittingUnpeeledBody;
153 }
154
155 PeelingStatus peeling_ = PeelingStatus::kNotPeeling;
156 const Block* current_loop_header_ = nullptr;
157
158 LoopFinder loop_finder_{__ phase_zone(), &__ modifiable_input_graph()};
159 JSHeapBroker* broker_ = __ data() -> broker();
160};
161

163
164} // namespace v8::internal::compiler::turboshaft
